heaviest_rainfall.status: The storm today is ranked 7th for the amount of rainfall recorded during one storm.  23.86mm fell at a maximum rate of 8.3mm per hour over 31.0 hours.  The most intense rainfall recorded took place on 09 November 2025, with precipitation totalling 47.89mm.  The rain fell at 24.6mm per hour at times over the course of the 144.8 hour storm.

heaviest_rainrate.status: 27.6mm per hour was the peak rain rate recorded today ranking 2nd in our overall records.  The storm lasted 2.6 hours and 6.1mm of rain fell.  The heaviest rain rate registered stands at 34.3mm per hour on 02 September 2025, highlighting an extreme precipitation event.  21.19mm fell during the storm over 15.0 hours.

longest_rain.status: The storm today ranked 7th for the length of the storm when compared to others in our records and it lasted 31.0 hours.  23.86mm of rain fell and at one point was falling at 8.3mm per hour.  Rain fell for 144.8 hours on 09 November 2025 creating a new record that still lasts.  The storm produced a total of 47.89mm with a maximum intensity of 24.6mm per hour.
